	<h2>Select Source Device</h2>
</div>
TPL_REQUIRE_2
<div id="wrap">
	<p>For this step, select a pair of headphones (or other sound output) that you do <strong>not</strong> need when streaming.</p>
	<p><a href="/page/music?reload" onclick="return plswait();">Perform a rescan</a> if you have connected or disconnected any speakers or headphones recently.</p>
	
	<hr />
	
	<p>If you want more options, look for an extra LineOut-jack or <br />headphone socket on your computer. Find something to <br />plug in there, headphones or whatever.</p>
	<p>You may also need to enable the output in MS Windows'<br />
	<a href="/page/music?cp">Control Panel for sound</a> (rightclick everything and select Enable).</p>
	<p>Remember, after any modifications, <a href="/page/music?reload" onclick="return plswait();">perform a rescan</a> to detect the changes.</p>
	<p>One final note: Speakers in HDMI screens do work, but are not recommended<br />due to slightly more work during the next step.</p>
	
	<hr />
	
	<p>Earlier, you selected this as your primary sound device:<br />
	<strong>TPL_OUT_DEV</strong></p>
	<p>These are the <em>other</em> available (plugged in and working) headphones and speakers.</p>
